370
00:20:07,353 --> 00:20:09,311
Norman: Let's escape, Emma.

371
00:20:09,395 --> 00:20:10,978
We'll get out of here.

372
00:20:11,061 --> 00:20:13,270
That's right. We can do it.

373
00:20:13,353 --> 00:20:15,561
Between you, me, and ray...

374
00:20:15,645 --> 00:20:17,436
Emma: And the others,
what about them?

375
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:19,728
( Sobs ) I can't leave them.

376
00:20:19,811 --> 00:20:22,811
If we do,
they'll all be killed for sure.

377
00:20:22,895 --> 00:20:24,645
I can't take it.

378
00:20:24,728 --> 00:20:26,686
I don't want to lose
any more family.

379
00:20:26,770 --> 00:20:28,145
( Norman shudders )

380
00:20:28,228 --> 00:20:29,853
( Hummed melody continues )

381
00:20:33,395 --> 00:20:36,728
And you won't have to.

382
00:20:36,811 --> 00:20:37,478
( Emma gasps )

383
00:20:41,436 --> 00:20:42,936
Norman: Try not to worry.

384
00:20:43,020 --> 00:20:45,103
We'll flee, all of us.

385
00:20:45,186 --> 00:20:47,561
Emma: Really? But how?

386
00:20:47,645 --> 00:20:50,895
How can a bunch of kids
run away from those monsters?

387
00:20:58,270 --> 00:21:00,061
( Gasps ) Strategy,

388
00:21:00,145 --> 00:21:01,728
like when we played tag.

389
00:21:01,811 --> 00:21:04,228
Norman: Right.
We will find a way,

390
00:21:04,311 --> 00:21:06,645
one that ensures
all of us survive.

391
00:21:07,853 --> 00:21:09,103
( Emma grunts )

392
00:21:09,186 --> 00:21:10,811
( Hummed melody continues )

393
